name: io.bytes.per.checksum
description:
The number of bytes per checksum.  Must not be larger than
  io.file.buffer.size.

name: dfs.client.cached.conn.retry
description:
The number of times the HDFS client will pull a socket from the
   cache.  Once this number is exceeded, the client will try to create a new
   socket.

name: mapreduce.job.maps
description:
The default number of map tasks per job.
  Ignored when mapreduce.framework.name is "local".

name: ipc.[port_number].scheduler.priority.levels
description:
How many priority levels to use within the scheduler and call
    queue. This property applies to RpcScheduler and CallQueue.

name: yarn.app.mapreduce.am.container.log.limit.kb
description:
The maximum size of the MRAppMaster attempt container logs in KB.
    0 disables the cap.

name: dfs.datanode.cache.revocation.timeout.ms
description:
When the DFSClient reads from a block file which the DataNode is
    caching, the DFSClient can skip verifying checksums.  The DataNode will
    keep the block file in cache until the client is done.  If the client takes
    an unusually long time, though, the DataNode may need to evict the block
    file from the cache anyway.  This value controls how long the DataNode will
    wait for the client to release a replica that it is reading without
    checksums.
